com.samsung.android.service.health.tracking.data

Class ValueKey<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samsung.android.service.health.tracking.data.ValueKey<T>

  • public class ValueKey<T>
extends Object
    ValueKey represents data sets for each HealthTrackerType.

    Measured data is received with DataPoint in HealthTracker.TrackerEventListener.
    Get the measured data value through DataPoint.getValue(). 

       private final HealthTracker.TrackerEventListener biaTrackerEventListener = new HealthTracker.TrackerEventListener() {
     @Override
     public onDataReceived(List<DataPoint> data) {
         for(DataPoint dp : list) {
             Float bfr = dp.getValue(ValueKey.BiaSet.BODY_FAT_RATIO);
             Integer status = dp.getValue(ValueKey.BiaSet.STATUS);
         }
         // ...
     }

     @Override
     public void onFlushCompleted() {
         // ...
     }

     @Override
     public void onError(HealthTracker.TrackerError trackerError) {
         // ...
     }
 }

    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
